# Component Patterns

## File Organization

- **Shadcn primitives** go in `src/components/ui/` (managed by `npx shadcn add`)
- **Page sections** go in `src/components/sections/` (one file per section)
- **Shared components** go in `src/components/` root (navbar, footer, contact-form, theme-provider)
- New sections should follow: export a named function, wrap in `<section>` with an `id` and `scroll-mt-20`

## Component Template

```tsx
"use client";

import { motion } from "framer-motion";
import { SomeIcon } from "lucide-react";

export function MySectionName() {
  return (
    <section id="my-section" className="py-24 scroll-mt-20">
      <div className="mx-auto max-w-[857px] px-6 lg:px-12">
        {/* Section Heading */}
        <motion.div
          initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
          whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
          viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}
          transition={{ duration: 0.5 }}
          className="mb-20 flex items-center gap-3"
        >
          <div className="h-[2px] w-8 bg-cyan" />
          <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold text-foreground lg:text-4xl">
            Section Title
          </h2>
        </motion.div>
        {/* Content here */}
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

## Rules

- Use **named exports** (`export function Foo`), never `export default`
- Components needing browser APIs or hooks must start with `"use client"`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Compose classes with Tailwind utilities; avoid inline `style={}` props
- Icons from `lucide-react` are sized with `h-X w-X` classes, not the `size` prop
- Use Shadcn's `<Button>`, `<Input>`, `<Textarea>`, `<Label>` for form elements
